com.bmd.jrt.routine

Class ObjectRoutineBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bmd.jrt.routine.ClassRoutineBuilder
      • com.bmd.jrt.routine.ObjectRoutineBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RoutineBuilder

    public class ObjectRoutineBuilder
extends ClassRoutineBuilder
    Class implementing a builder of routines wrapping an object instance.

    Note that only instance methods can be asynchronously invoked through the routines created by this builder.

    Created by davide on 9/21/14.

    See Also:
    Async, AsyncType, ParallelType

      • implementationOf

        @Nonnull
public <CLASS> CLASS implementationOf(@Nonnull
                                     Class<CLASS> itf)
        Returns an object enabling asynchronous calls to the target instance methods.

        The routines used for calling the methods will honor the attributes specified in any optional Async, AsyncType and ParallelType annotations.
        The wrapping object is created through code generation based on the interfaces annotated with AsyncClass.
        Note that, you'll need to enable annotation pre-processing by adding the processor package to the specific project dependencies.

        Type Parameters:
        CLASS - the interface type.
        Parameters:
        itf - the interface implemented by the return object.
        Returns:
        the wrapping object.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified class is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified class does not represent an interface.

      • proxy

        @Nonnull
public <CLASS> CLASS proxy(@Nonnull
                          Class<CLASS> itf)
        Returns a proxy object enabling asynchronous calls to the target instance methods.

        The routines used for calling the methods will honor the attributes specified in any optional Async annotation.
        In case the wrapped object does not implement the specified interface, the value attribute will be used to bind the interface method with the instance ones. If no name is assigned the method name will be used instead to map it.
        The interface will be interpreted as a mirror of the target object methods, and the optional AsyncType and ParallelType annotations will be honored.

        Type Parameters:
        CLASS - the interface type.
        Parameters:
        itf - the interface implemented by the return object.
        Returns:
        the proxy object.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified class is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified class does not represent an interface.
